            }
          ],
          "name": "Other Grim Champions",
          "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
          "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "NPC Core pg. 156",
                "aonid": 236,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "NPC Core pg. 156",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "NPC Core",
              "page": 156,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "The most sinister champions of unholy gods are devoted to desecration or iniquity. This champion serves Rovagug, but Lamashtu, Urgathoa, and demon lords have similar champions. If you switch their deity, change their favored weapon (see the Deity table). If it's a one-handed weapon, reduce the champion's AC by 2, give them a steel shield, and replace Axe Swipe with Defensive Advance, a 2-action activity that lets the champion Raise their Shield, Stride, and make a melee Strike.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "NPC Core pg. 156",
            "aonid": 236,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "NPC Core pg. 156",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "NPC Core",
          "page": 156,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "There are perhaps no mortals more anathematic to peace than champions of Rovagug or other destructive deities.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
